U.S. Push for Closer Military Tie-up with "Allies" under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 31 (KCNA) -- The United States is these days tightening military collusion with its "allies." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some time ago, the U.S. installed its first mobile missile tracking devices in Japan under the pretext of coping with the "missile threat" from the DPRK. U.S. troops are said to be posted at the joint ground tactical control station, which is a mobile information processing system deployed in Japan, to perform the duty of watching the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the other hand, the U.S. agreed with Israel to jointly develop a multistage missile defense system to intercept "long- and short-range missiles from Iran and Syria".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, a news analyst of Minju Joson Wednesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is proof of the desperate efforts of the U.S. to grab a definite military strategic edge at strategic vantages by the means of reinforcing the military cooperation system with its "allies." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. seeks to guarantee its monopolistic domination at strategic vantages worldwide by keeping a tight military grip on its "allies" in Northeast Asia and Middle East where the thrust of big powers is noticeably intensified. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 It is the strategic consideration of the U.S. that it could constantly ensure its military influence in the given areas, if it bound Japan and Israel to a "military cooperation" system dubbed missile defence system under the cloak of their "security." This is the reason why the U.S. is kicking up quite a dust in establishing missile tracking devices in Japan and jointly developing a system for intercepting long- and short-range missiles with Israel under the pretext of "missile threat" from the DPRK, Iran and Syria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This proves that there is no change in the real nature of the U.S. in seeking to dominate the world with strength. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The policy of military standoff and strategy for world supremacy will bring only catastrophic consequences to the U.S. itself.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Spurs to Fulfilment of Three Tasks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 31 (KCNA) -- All the fellow countrymen in the north, the south and overseas should wage an intensive struggle to fulfil the three tasks--attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity--with confidence in and optimism about national reunification and thus brilliantly adorn the movement for national reunification in this significant year, urges Rodong Sinmun in an article Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unanimous will of the members of the Korean nation to discharge their obligation and duty for the era and history by constantly putting spurs to the fulfilment of the three tasks, the author of the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stand of attaching importance to the nation should be firmly maintained. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the basic stand the Korean nation should invariably maintain in the struggle to achieve national reunification as it is forced to the tragedy of national division by foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle for defending peace should be vigorously waged incessantly to thwart and frustrate the imperialist forces' moves for aggression and war and defend the peace of the country and the security of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reunification of the country and the prosperity of the nation would be unthinkable without the struggle against aggression and war moves. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun policy serves as a patriotic treasured sword for defending peace on the Korean Peninsula and the security of the nation and guaranteeing the victory of the movement for independent reunification. The Korean nation should absolutely support and firmly defend the Songun policy the validity and vitality of which have been fully proven in the practical struggle to defend peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Work should be done in high gear to achieve the unity of the whole nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There will be nothing fearful or impossible on earth, if all the fellow countrymen in the north, the south and overseas are closely united as one with the concerted efforts of the nation, regardless of differences in idea and ideal, political view, religious belief, class and stratum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the fellow countrymen at home and abroad should be firmly united in the spirit of "By our nation itself".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the pride and awareness of living in the era of independent reunification, the whole nation should continue to upgrade the atmosphere of national reconciliation and unity and lift the solidarity and alliance of the organizations for the reunification movement to a new, higher stage with the June 15 All-Korean Committee as the mother body.

ATCC critica peticion miserable de Japon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 31 de octubre (ATCC) -- Japon se porta mal pretextando el "problema del secuestro". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Hace poco tiempo, el canciller japones Komura solicito al embajador estadounidense acreditado en su pais que mientras que no se logre avance en la solucion del "problema del secuestro" posponga borrar al Norte de Corea de la lista de "paises que apoyan al terrorismo". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La llamada "federacion de parlamentarios por el problema del secuestro", integrada por los bicamerales ultrapartidistas, tambien pidio la cooperacion de otros paises en el mismo asunto, diciendo que ahora se necesita mas que nunca ejercer presion al Norte de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tal conducta astuta y descarada es propia para el pais isleno acostumbrado a acusar a otro pais y desviar la opinion publica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Antes de hablar del "problema del secuestro" Japon tiene el deber legal y moral de saldar su pasado criminal por haber cometido los crimenes de arresto forzoso a los coreanos y de "consoladoras sexuales" para el viejo ejercito japones y acarreado otras incontables desgracias y sufrimientos al pueblo coreano. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Sin embargo, sin hablar de su pasado lleno de crimenes, induce en error la opinion publica como si fuera "victima" su pais e insiste obstinadamente en el ya solucionado "problema del secuestro".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La verdadera intencion de Japon es evadir de todos modos la responsabilidad por la liquidacion del pasado criminal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Pero, la realidad demuestra que cuanto mas cuestione Japon el "problema del secuestro", tanto mas se denigrara su reputacion politica y moral y se aislara en la arena internacional.

Minju Joson revela la confabulacion militar de EE.UU. y sus "aliados"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 31 de octubre (ATCC) -- En estos dias Estados Unidos da espuelas a la confabulacion militar con sus "paises aliados".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Hace poco, bajo el pretexto de "hacer frente a la amenaza de misiles" de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea EE.UU. instalo por primera vez en Japon el aparato movil de persecucion a misiles. En el centro de control terrestre de tactica conjunta que es el sistema movil de tratamiento de informaciones emplazado en ese pais isleno las tropas norteamericanas cumpliran la mision de vigilancia a la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por otra parte, logro un acuerdo con Israel de desarrollar en comun el sistema antimisiles de diferentes alturas para interceptar los "misiles de largo y corto alcance de Iran y Siria".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esto demuestra que a traves del fortalecimiento del sistema de cooperacion militar con los "paises aliados" el imperio se esfuerza desesperadamente por ocupar la segura supremacia militar en los nudos estrategicos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Minju Joson en un comentario individual de este miercoles y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  EE.UU. trata de controlar militarmente a sus "aliados" situados en el Nordeste Asiatico y el Medio Oriente a donde dirigen miradas codiciosas las potencias para asi afianzar su control monopolista sobre los nudos estrategicos del mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El tiene calculo estrategico de ejercer sostenidamente su influencia militar sobre las regiones arriba mencionadas por medio de incorporar Japon e Israel al sistema de la "cooperacion militar" en el establecimiento del sistema antimisiles bajo el pretexto de la "seguridad" de estos ambos paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He aqui el motivo por el cual EE.UU. se ajetrea para emplazar el aparato de persecucion a misiles en Japon e Israel y desarrollar juntos el sistema antimisiles bajo el pretexto de la "amenaza de misiles" de Corea, Iran y Siria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esto demuestra que es invariable la naturaleza de EE.UU. de dominar con la fuerza el mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La politica de enfrentamiento militar y la estrategia de heguemonia mundial traeran solo la autodestruccion de EE.UU.
